Package com.tsgrp.migration.event.target

The target event package.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    NodeContentFileWriterListener
    Based on a configured attribute name, save content from the given node into a file location specified in the given Node Attribute (default is "om_target_file_location").
    NodeRenditionFileWriterListener
    Save the associated renditions of a migration node to the filesystem.
    StoreAttrListener
    Stores the an old to new value translation using the values of the injected attributes of a newly created object (and associated versions) in an injected Rosetta repository.
    StoreIdListener
    Stores the old and new object IDs of a newly created object (and associated versions) in an injected Rosetta repository
    TargetCsvWriterListener
    Writes out completed nodes to a data file
    TranslateAttrListener
    Inspects incoming migration nodes for attributes to be translated.
    TranslateIdListener
    Inspects incoming migration nodes for ID attributes.
    UpdateNodeStatusMigratedListener
    Do one thing: update a node's status to MIGRATED.
    UpdateNodeStatusRemovedListener
    Do one thing: update a node's status to REMOVED.
    WatchFolderFileRemoverListener
    Cleans up the lock files and the source item (assumes path is provided by MigrationNode.RESERVED_SOURCE_FILE_PATH attribute) from the filesystem.
